<refbody>
<section><p>This close match of simpletable to tabular, regular data makes
simpletable suitable as the basis for specialized structures such as <xref
href="properties.dita">properties</xref> (for programming information) and <xref
href="choicetable.dita">choice tables</xref> (for tasks).</p></section>
<example><title>Example</title><dl><dlentry>
<dt>Source: </dt>
<dd><codeblock>&lt;simpletable&gt;
 &lt;sthead&gt;
  &lt;stentry&gt;Type style&lt;/stentry&gt;
  &lt;stentry&gt;Elements used&lt;/stentry&gt;
 &lt;/sthead&gt;
 &lt;strow&gt;
  &lt;stentry&gt;Bold&lt;/stentry&gt;
  &lt;stentry&gt;b&lt;/stentry&gt;
 &lt;/strow&gt;
 &lt;strow&gt;
  &lt;stentry&gt;Italic&lt;/stentry&gt;
  &lt;stentry&gt;i&lt;/stentry&gt;
 &lt;/strow&gt;
 &lt;strow&gt;
  &lt;stentry&gt;Underlined&lt;/stentry&gt;
  &lt;stentry&gt;u&lt;/stentry&gt;
 &lt;/strow&gt;
&lt;/simpletable&gt;</codeblock></dd>
</dlentry><dlentry>
<dt>Formatted output:</dt>
<dd><simpletable relcolwidth="2* 2*">
<sthead>
<stentry>Type style</stentry>
<stentry>Elements used</stentry>
</sthead>
<strow>
<stentry>Bold</stentry>
<stentry>b</stentry>
</strow>
<strow>
<stentry>Italic</stentry>
<stentry>i</stentry>
</strow>
<strow>
<stentry>Underlined</stentry>
<stentry>u</stentry>
</strow>
</simpletable></dd>
</dlentry></dl></example>
